Happy holidays from the Cases 💚

16 hours of travel with two under two, lots of presents & huge energy for Santa Claus to show up…

1) Cash got a new 4-wheeler
2) we watched the Grinch 100x
3) Cruz loved his first Christmas 
4) Mom & daddy got extra sleep 🙏
5) God is good!

Thanks Gigi & Grand dude for all the fun. Back to Florida we go!!!

HAPPY BIRTHDAY to my firstborn, Cash Case 💚 TWO years old ‼️

We love you so much little man. Just a few years ago you changed our world. You made us parents. We gained a lot of patience & even more chaos! You are confident, crazy, full of energy, never meet a stranger, funny, know exactly what you want when you want it, a great big brother to Cruz, & you keep us on our toes 100%. I couldn’t imagine my life without you. My first son! My little man & best friend. I am so blessed to call you mine.

I pray you keep being exactly who God made you to be. You are loved by so many 🎈thankful for our community near & far that loves Cash so well!

EASTER LIVIN 💜 photo dump…

Jesus is the hope of the world. Grateful to have family, friends & a special community in our lives.

Whatever you’re going through in life, I want to remind you that God’s not done. Nothing will be wasted. 

You are loved. You have purpose. Choose to keep going 🚀

28 POUNDS LOST 🏆 @_owentreadwell_ 

The journey is not easy but it’s worth it. Everything is EARNED. @bulletproof_humans 

Where we started: 257lbs 🔺
Not happy, wanted change, only able to do 1 push-up.

Where we are now: 227lbs 🚀🟢
Confident, strong, food habits, weekly workouts, outdoor runs & MORE.

Believe in YOURSELF. Check out what he said below…👇

“I started BHP Coaching in August. I wasn’t happy with myself. I wanted to change. Carson met with me about weight goals, personal goals, mental goals & changing my habits. We got to work & never looked back. Training started 5x weekly. I immediately began to lose weight & see changes in my life! Carson continued to coach me through the holidays & into the new year 2023. We started this season strong & I began to fall in love with running. We would add shorter runs during the week & run distance on the weekends. I keep getting better & better. Today I am in the BEST SHAPE OF MY LIFE.

I started with 1 push-up.
Now I can do 32+. ✅

Last year I ran a 12 min mile.
Now I can run a 9 min mile & improving. ✅

My life is totally different 🔥

Committing to @bulletproof_humans has been one of the best things I’ve ever done & I’d recommend this to anyone.”

LET’S GO. This is why I coach men to be disciplined & become all they can be. 

If you need a complete change to your fitness, mindset & lifestyle - DM ME now.

STOP WAITING ❤️‍🔥

GRATEFUL but HUNGRY 🤎

these last few months have come with blessings, breakthroughs, hard days, lessons, love, grace & growth. I vow to keep growing!

You’re a product of your environment. Keep positive & inspiring people around you.

LET’S RIDE.

MEN, MINDSET, LIFESTYLE.

I’ve always been drawn to personal development & intense community around being the BEST MAN you can be. That’s what BHP x RED DOT is becoming. Create space. Get focused. Get honest. Lead. Learn & grow. We want men all over the world to have the right community to invest in themselves, their future & family. God has MORE for us.

Is this for You?

You want more out of life! Average is not it for you. You are hungry. You desire to build your body, mind & soul. You have dreams. You need a place to focus. You need accountability. You just need to light a fire in your heart. JUNE 1-4, Orlando 🐺

We are hosting a weekend for guys interested in this type of life. Faith, fitness, fun, family, business & MORE.

RED DOT 🔴 come grow with us & a like minded crew. This will be the perfect way to super charge your mindset for your next SZN of life. 

DM ME if interested & let’s hop on a call.

MARRIAGE MINDSET 🫶🏼

We don’t have it all figured out but here’s a few things I’ve loved & picked up over the years. Still dating. Raising kids. Growing. Building biz. Following Jesus. Winning. Failing.👇

1. love God & love your family with all your heart, mind & soul.
2. Laugh a lot & laugh at yourself, most things you’re worried about now aren’t important.
3. Be YOU & don’t let anyone tell you different, the world needs You.
4. Dream big & never quit.
5. Embrace the future & know you guys will make mistakes along the way.
6. Think about others, serve them, love them & invite them into your story. THIS is what matters.
7. Know your WHY & reflect on this often. Your WHY is what will carry you when the way seems unknown.

This is our best life 🚀

WEDNESDAY 6AM EST 🧡

30 miles. 3,000 reps. No quit. Challenges are meant to be embraced & sharpen us to become the best we can be. I know this is physically & mentally not an easy task, which is why I’m on a mission tomorrow to bring awareness to infertility & the realities couples all over the world are facing. You are not alone. Bulletproof In the Arena will be dedicated to this cause. Join me. Follow along on my Instagram story & spread the word.

THE DETAILS ❤️‍🔥 APRIL 26 🐺

This is a full workout grid & mileage outlook for everything Bulletproof in the Arena. Join me tomorrow for reps & miles. The work will start at 6AM. Anyone is welcome to jump in, share & spread the word. My current outlook is a 6 part day.

Part 1: 6AM
Part 2: 830AM
Part 3: 11AM
Part 4: 2PM
Part 5: 430PM
Part 6: FINISH

I know many of you have texted, DM’d & ask how to join. Use these reps. Track 1 mile or many more. Whatever it takes to push yourself & welcome the difficulty of this. The purpose is much bigger than me. Our hope is to bring as much awareness to infertility as we can. All donations will go towards research, resources & treatment partnered with foundations here in Orlando, FL.

SPREAD THE WORD 🖤 donation link in bio.

MORNING UPDATE ❤️‍🔥👇

Just getting started.

The body will follow.

OUR FOUNDATION 💗

Heart. Home. Health. A few key things you remind us of constantly babe. Being a Mama & doing it with the grace that you do, I’ll never understand. Your heart is big. MY KIND OF TRAINING 👇 

1) functional: I want to be able to move. I want to be strong, look good, feel good, be fast if needed & still get better every day. When I think about the gym & training - I want it to be able to translate into my real world. It’s more than just looking good in a picture. This is lifestyle! My Biz. My marriage. My kids. My home. All of it 💜

2) creativity: the biggest thing I hear is people get bored in the gym & quit training. Full body thinking allows you to work all planes of motion, work fast twitch, flow, high intensity, whatever else depending on the day. Get creative but be intentional with what you’re doing. Your body is capable of SO MUCH. It’s a journey.

3) mental: I really believe training my Full body through many sessions during the week pushes the mindset to new levels. Transitioning from upper, to lower, to lungs, to quick, single leg, body weight or even heavy… brings a challenge to not only your body but your BRAIN. Pushing my helps me get better. Confidence goes up. You know that lord is possible. You get sharper for the next day. 

Your training can come in many forms. Some days we can focus on being strong in hitting the main, basic lifts. Other days we can move quick & hit bodyweight. We can also really challenge our body/mind with very specific things. Sleds. KB. DB. Bars. Ropes. Run. Bike. Row. Etc.

It’s personal! What are your goals? Are you training for something! How do you like to feel? Is your fitness focus short or long term? Are you married, have kids?! How important is health to you?

Have fun with it! Be a little bit better every day. You can start NOW. 

Your fitness upgrades your leadership in every area of life!

I changed my life by changing my habits. Here are a few things we have adopted in recent years to become healthy & create a home we love. 

It’s never easy setting big goals without clear direction. It only takes one thing. Then another thing. Stop trying to create the life you desire without adding the habits to get you there. 

Show me your habits & I’ll show you your future❤️‍🔥

MY FIRST RACE 🏆

“HYROX Chicago” was something I found a few months ago & decided to sign up right then. With a background in athletics, but an intensive back surgery in high school, it scared me to compete at a high level like this. I was hurt for a long time. I lost a lot of confidence in my body. I am busy. I could come up with a million excuses. 

But why not test yourself? I had no clue what I was getting into but loved the idea. If you say you’re going to do something, you have to do it. 

Here’s a few things I learned after failing at my expectations:

1) do hard things or die wishing you did.
2) most of our battles are mental, not physical.
3) you may be a beast, but there are always bigger beasts.
4) losing builds character.
5) you are either prepared or you are not.
6) everything is earned.
7) quitting in life is not an option.
8) there’s bad, average, good, excellent, and elite. Choose!
9) give yourself grace but stay hungry
10) sign up for the thing & finish it.

This was such a humbling experience for me. I’ve never been a runner, but I like sprinting. I failed big at running long distances to prep for this. You feel fit & then you run into people who are better than you. These are lessons learned. I led this race for 14 minutes then fell off hard because I lacked endurance, more training & dealt with a ton of cramping.

Thank you God for an able body & a Bulletproof mindset.

My goal is to be the best I can be every day. Set a great standard for myself, family & friends. Lead by example. Follow through with my commitments. Lead. Train. Learn. Repeat. I want to inspire those around me to push yourself & do hard things, because you can. Keep going. Anything is possible.

I can’t wait to sign up for New York City & prove myself right. Be willing to get better! And you will.

Final stats:
250+ hours of training
Lifting 5-6x weekly
Running 3x weekly

42nd in my age group 
310th overall out of A LOT of people.

Great experience. Back to the drawing board 🤎
